HEADWORD: Excito-secretory
<hw>Ex*ci`to-se*cre"to*ry</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<fld>(Physiol.)</fld> <def>Exciting secretion; -- said of the influence
exerted by reflex action on the function of secretion, by which the
various glands are excited to action.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

